### Code Examples
Always include:
- Syntax highlighting (```typescript, ```tsx, ```javascript, etc.)
- Context (what component, what file)
- Comments explaining key parts

### UI/UX Documentation
- Include before/after comparisons
- Show user interaction flows
- Document state changes
- Explain visual design decisions

### Tables
Use tables for comparisons:
```markdown
| Feature | Before | After |
|---------|--------|-------|
| Panel display | Static | Dynamic updates |
```

### Language
- Write in present tense
- Be clear and concise
- Explain "what" and "why", not just "how"
- Assume reader has React/TypeScript context
- Define acronyms on first use

